## Project Planning Guidelines

### Product Requirements Document (PRD):
- Create comprehensive PRDs with clear sections:
  - Product overview
  - User problems
  - Functional requirements
  - Project scope boundaries
  - User stories
  - Success metrics

### User Stories:
- Write testable user stories with acceptance criteria
- Use consistent format: ID, Title, Description, Acceptance Criteria
- Cover basic, alternative, and edge case scenarios
- Include authentication/authorization stories when applicable

### Planning Process:
- Analyze project ideas and technical stack compatibility
- Conduct thorough requirement analysis sessions
- Document decisions and rationale
- Create proof-of-concepts for critical functionality

### Documentation:
- Maintain comprehensive README with:
  - Project description
  - Tech stack details
  - Local setup instructions
  - Available scripts
  - Project scope and status

### Quality Assurance:
- Ensure all user stories are testable
- Define clear acceptance criteria
- Plan for authentication and security requirements
- Consider edge cases and error scenarios